  "prompt": "How do you use Google Account Recovery to reset your password?",
  "response": "To reset your password using Google Account Recovery, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Go to the Sign-In page**:\n   - Open your web browser and go to the Google Sign-In page: [https://accounts.google.com/](https://accounts.google.com/).\n\n2. **Click on \u2018Forgot password?\u2019**:\n   - Enter your email address and click \u201cNext.\u201d If you've forgotten your email, click on \u201cForgot email?\u201d and follow the prompts to recover it.\n   - On the next page, click on the \u201cForgot password?\u201d option.\n\n3. **Select Recovery Option**:\n   - Google will prompt you to enter the last password you remember. If you do not remember any, click on \u201cTry another way.\u201d\n   - Google may offer various recovery options, such as sending a verification code to your registered phone number or your recovery email address.\n\n4. **Verify Your Identity**:\n   - Choose a recovery option and follow the instructions. If you receive a verification code, enter it in the prompted field. If it's sent to your phone, make sure you have access to that device.\n\n5. **Set a New Password**:\n   - Once your identity is verified, you will be prompted to create a new password. Choose a strong and unique password that you haven\u2019t used before.\n\n6. **Sign in with the New Password**:\n   - After resetting your password, you can sign in to your Google Account with your new password.\n\n7. **Review Security Settings**:\n   - It\u2019s a good idea to check your security settings after resetting your password. This can include adding recovery options like a phone number or secondary email for future recovery.\n\nIf you have trouble recovering your account, Google provides additional recovery options and support on their help page: [Google Account Recovery Help](https://support.google.com/accounts/answer/7682439).",
